openapi: 3.0.3
info:

    name: Apache 2.0
    url: https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0
  title: FactSet Fundamentals Report Builder
  version: 1.0.0
externalDocs:
  description: Read more about STACH 2.0's row organized schema
  url: https://factset.github.io/stachschema/#/v2/RowOrganized

paths:
  /income-statement:
    get:
      description: Returns a standardized Income Statement based on industry.
      operationId: getFinancialsIncomeStatement
      parameters:
      - description: Company Ticker
        explode: true
        in: query
        name: id
        required: true
        schema:
          example: FDS
          type: string
        style: form
      - description: Periodicity or frequency of the fiscal periods.
        explode: true
        in: query
        name: periodicity
        required: false
        schema:
          default: INTERIM
          enum:
          - ANN
          - QTR
          - SEMI
          - INTERIM
          - CAL
          type: string
        style: form
      - description: |
          The schema that the data is returned as. The following are descriptions for the accepted values:
          - table_group_level - STACH 2.0 row organized package format with parent-child relationships represented using STACH group level cell metadata
          - table_parent_child_columns - STACH 2.0 row organized package format with parent-child relationships represented using STACH parent-child columns
        explode: true
        in: query
        name: schema
        required: false
        schema:
          default: table_parent_child_columns
          enum:
          - table_group_level
          - table_parent_child_columns
          type: string
        style: form
      - description: "Return historical periods as originally reported or retroactively\
          \ restated (for M&A, accounting changes, and other events). The following\
          \ are descriptions for the accepted values:\n- RESTATED - retroactively\
          \ restated data.\n- NON-RESTATED - originally reported data. \n"
        explode: true
        in: query
        name: reportStatus
        required: false
        schema:
          default: RESTATED
          enum:
          - RESTATED
          - NON-RESTATED
          type: string
        style: form
      - description: |
          Currency code for currency values. "LOCAL" will return the security's pricing currency. "RPT" will return the company's reporting currency (which may differ from "LOCAL" for some companies). For a list of other currency ISO codes, visit Online Assistant Page [OA1470](https://my.apps.factset.com/oa/pages/1470).
        explode: true
        in: query
        name: currency
        required: false
        schema:
          default: LOCAL
          type: string
        style: form
      responses:
        "200":
          content:
            application/json:
              examples:
                groupLevelResponse:
                  $ref: '#/components/examples/groupLevelResponse'
                parentChildColumnsResponse:
                  $ref: '#/components/examples/parentChildColumnsResponse'
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/Response'
          description: Expected response; returns JSON data containing STACH 2.0 row
            organized package format
          headers:
            X-DataDirect-Request-Key:
              description: FactSet request ID
              explode: false
              schema:
                type: string
              style: simple
            Api-Supported-Versions:
              description: Supported API major versions
              explode: false
              schema:
                type: string
              style: simple
            Api-Version:
              description: API version (semantic versioning)
              explode: false
              schema:
                type: string
              style: simple
        "400":

            application/json:
              examples:
                idRequiredParameterError:
                  $ref: '#/components/examples/idRequiredParameterError'
                idInvalidParameterError:
                  $ref: '#/components/examples/idInvalidParameterError'
                parameterErrorPeriodicity:
                  $ref: '#/components/examples/parameterErrorPeriodicity'
                parameterErrorReportStatus:
                  $ref: '#/components/examples/parameterErrorReportStatus'
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/ErrorResponse'
          description: Bad Request. For further assistance, file an issue under "Workflow
            & Throttling - 400 or 429 Response" using `Report Issue` at the top of
            this page, including the X-DataDirect-Request-Key from the header to assist
            in troubleshooting.
          headers:
            X-DataDirect-Request-Key:
              description: FactSet request ID
              explode: false
              schema:
                type: string
              style: simple
            Api-Supported-Versions:
              description: Supported API major versions
              explode: false
              schema:
                type: string
              style: simple
            Api-Version:
              description: API version (semantic versioning)
              explode: false
              schema:
                type: string
              style: simple
        "401":
          description: Missing or invalid authentication. Ensure you are logged in
            and have successfully generated an API KEY for the IP range you are connecting
            from. For further assistance, file an issue under "Connectivty - 401 or
            403 Responses" using `Report Issue` at the top of this page, including
            the X-DataDirect-Request-Key from the header to assist in troubleshooting.
          headers:
            X-DataDirect-Request-Key:
              description: FactSet request ID
              explode: false
              schema:
                type: string
              style: simple
        "403":
          content:
            application/json:
              examples:
                notAuthorized:
                  $ref: '#/components/examples/notAuthorized'
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/ErrorResponse'
          description: User is forbidden access with current credentials. Reach out
            to your local FactSet Account Manager for assistance, or file an issue
            under "Connectivty - 401 or 403 Responses" using `Report Issue` at the
            top of this page, including the X-DataDirect-Request-Key from the header
            to assist in troubleshooting.
          headers:
            X-DataDirect-Request-Key:
              description: FactSet request ID
              explode: false
              schema:
                type: string
              style: simple
        "404":
          content:
            application/json:
              examples:
                endpointNotFound:

              schema:

          headers:

                type: string
              style: simple

          description: Too many requests - this API is rate-limited to 20 requests

              explode: false

              style: simple
